idCitation.resTitle: Proposed Sea Change Marine Protection Areas - June2021

dataIdInfo.idPurp: Revitalising the Gulf - Government action on the Sea Change Plan
dataIdInfo.idAbs: To deliver on the Sea Change planning process, it is proposed to: establish 11 new High Protection Areas and 5 Seafloor Protection Areas, and establish additional marine protection areas adjacent to existing no-take marine reserves. The polygons included in this data are the proposals included in the government document "Revitalising the Gulf - Government action on the Sea Change Plan", that can be downloaded at: https://www.doc.govt.nz/globalassets/documents/our-work/sea-change/revitalising-the-gulf.pdf
